    <fr:title text="The initial reflection algebra">The initial reflection algebra</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {U}\in \mathcal {V}]]></fr:tex> be an impredicative pair of universes with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A:\mathcal {V}]]></fr:tex>. There we may construct a  <fr:link href="jms-003O.xml" title="Reflection algebras and homomorphisms" addr="jms-003O" type="local">reflection algebra</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A_{\mathcal {U}} :{A}\downarrow {\mathcal {U}}]]></fr:tex> such that for any other <fr:link href="jms-003O.xml" title="Reflection algebras and homomorphisms" addr="jms-003O" type="local">reflection algebra</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X:{A}\downarrow {\mathcal {U}}]]></fr:tex>, the space of <fr:link href="jms-003O.xml" title="Reflection algebras and homomorphisms" addr="jms-003O" type="local">homomorphisms</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A_{\mathcal {U}}\multimap  X]]></fr:tex> is contractible.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>3</fr:month><fr:day>22</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>11038</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="machine">unstable/2471</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-2471.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:p>Our <fr:link href="jms-0044.xml" title="Splitting the generic element of the generic cone" addr="jms-0044" type="local">splitting of the generic element of the generic cone</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\Delta  I}\xrightarrow {{p}}{1_{{A}\downarrow {\mathcal {U}}}}]]></fr:tex> over the identity functor on reflection algebras <fr:link href="jms-003E.xml" title="A wild universal cone from a splitting of the generic element" addr="jms-003E" type="local">yields a new (incoherent) cone</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\Delta  J}\xrightarrow {{q}}{1_{{A}\downarrow {\mathcal {U}}}}]]></fr:tex> whose generic element <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q_{J}:J\multimap  J]]></fr:tex> may be identified with the identity homomorphism. It <fr:link href="jms-003B.xml" title="Wild initial objects from universal cones" addr="jms-003B" type="local">follows</fr:link> that each  space of homomorphisms <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[J\to  X]]></fr:tex> is contractible. Therefore, we define <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A_{\mathcal {U}}]]></fr:tex> to be the apex <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[J]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
